title: 1  Introduction
text:
This notebook contains notes on using python for data science and research.

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

v0 = 5
g = 9.81
t = np.linspace(0, 1, 1001)

y = v0*t - 0.5*g*t**2

plt.plot(t, y)
plt.xlabel('t (s)')
plt.ylabel('y (s)')
plt.show()
